  abstract  = "Until recently, calculations of one-electron Green functions
               within the $\mathrm{GW}$ approximation have been performed
               without self-consistency. Recent self-consistent $\mathrm{GW}$
               calculations for the electron gas suggest that vertex corrections
               are important in a self-consistent scheme. While the
               $\mathrm{GW}$ approximation gives good description for the
