  abstract  = "Coupled-cluster theory is a ``gold standard'' of molecular
               quantum chemistry, but has only recently been extended to
               condensed-phase systems. In this work, excited-state
               coupled-cluster techniques are brought to bear on the spectral
               function of the uniform electron gas. The diagrammatic content of
               coupled-cluster theory goes beyond that of the
               $G\phantom{\rule{0}{0ex}}W$ approximation, which has become a
